  <compounddef id="MEMFREE" kind="page">
    <compoundname>MEMFREE</compoundname>
    <title>MEMFREE Function</title>
    <briefdescription>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para><programlisting filename=".basic"><codeline><highlight class="normal">MEMFREE</highlight></codeline>
</programlisting></para>
<para>Returns the total amount of <bold>free memory</bold> available to BASIC programs and the operating system, in <bold>bytes</bold>.</para>
<para><hruler/>
</para>
<sect3 id="MEMFREE_1autotoc_md273">
<title>Examples</title>
<para><programlisting filename=".basic"><codeline><highlight class="normal">REM<sp/>Print<sp/>free<sp/>memory</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">PRINT<sp/>MEMFREE</highlight></codeline>
</programlisting></para>
<para>On a 4 GB machine with3.5 GB available, this might print:</para>
<para><programlisting><codeline><highlight class="normal">3758096384</highlight></codeline>
</programlisting></para>
<para><programlisting filename=".basic"><codeline><highlight class="normal">REM<sp/>Convert<sp/>to<sp/>megabytes<sp/>for<sp/>easier<sp/>reading</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">PRINT<sp/>MEMFREE<sp/>/<sp/>(1024<sp/>*<sp/>1024);<sp/>&quot;<sp/>MB<sp/>free&quot;</highlight></codeline>
</programlisting></para>
<para>On the same 4 GB machine, this might print:</para>
<para><programlisting><codeline><highlight class="normal">3584<sp/>MB<sp/>free</highlight></codeline>
</programlisting></para>
<para><programlisting filename=".basic"><codeline><highlight class="normal">REM<sp/>Simple<sp/>check<sp/>for<sp/>low<sp/>memory</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">IF<sp/>MEMFREE<sp/>&lt;<sp/>(512<sp/>*<sp/>1024<sp/>*<sp/>1024)<sp/>THEN</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal"><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/>PRINT<sp/>&quot;Warning:<sp/>less<sp/>than<sp/>512<sp/>MB<sp/>free&quot;</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">ENDIF</highlight></codeline>
</programlisting></para>
<para><hruler/>
</para>
</sect3>
<sect3 id="MEMFREE_1autotoc_md275">
<title>Notes</title>
<para><itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>The value is in <bold>bytes</bold>, returned as a 64-bit integer.</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Represents free space across the whole system (OS + BASIC).</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Actual available memory on a “4 GB” system is typically less than 4096 MB due to hardware reservations.</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>The value changes dynamically as programs allocate or free memory.</para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
<para><hruler/>
</para>
